---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How AdBunny's AI Banner Optimization Works"
  description="See exactly how AdBunny's single JS tag and AI optimization layer turn remnant ad inventory into revenue — step by step."
  keywords="how AI banner optimization works, ad tag integration, real-time banner optimization, ad monetization process"
>
<section class="page-header">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>From Empty Ad Slot to Optimized Revenue — Step by Step</h1>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="steps steps-single">
      <div class="step">
        <h3>Step 1 — Add the Tag</h3>
        <p>Paste a single JavaScript snippet into the pages or slots you want AdBunny to cover. No SDK, no server integration, no waterfall configuration.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <h3>Step 2 — AdBunny Evaluates Available Demand</h3>
        <p>When a covered slot loads, AdBunny's optimization layer evaluates the banner demand available for that specific impression in real time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <h3>Step 3 — The AI Selects the Best-Paying Banner</h3>
        <p>Rather than following a fixed, static call order, the system picks whichever available banner is likely to generate the most revenue for that impression, right now.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <h3>Step 4 — The Slot Fills, You Get Paid</h3>
        <p>The impression fills, and revenue starts flowing from inventory that used to sit empty or monetize at low, static rates.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="label">No Work Required</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">What You Don't Have to Do</h2>
    <div class="checklist-center">
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>No waterfall to build or maintain</li>
        <li>No line items to configure</li>
        <li>No manual optimization or A/B testing of network order</li>
        <li>No conflict with your existing primary demand</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>See It Running on Your Own Inventory</h2>
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Your JS Tag</a>
  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
